      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Systematic evaluation of turbulence model and hemolysis constitutive model form uncertainty; comparison of at least two model forms against experimental data.",
      "rationale": "Model form uncertainty was not assessed. A single turbulence closure (SST k-omega) and single hemolysis power-law model were used without comparison to alternative model forms. Critical gap at MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All uncertain model inputs characterized with probability distributions from experimental measurement or literature; Monte Carlo propagation performed to yield output uncertainty bounds on hemolysis QoI.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed propagating distributions for fluid viscosity, power-law hemolysis coefficients, and boundary flow rates across all 5 operating points. Output uncertainty bounds on hemolysis index are reported. However, no sensitivity analysis was conducted to identify which input parameters drive output variance, leaving the dominant contributors uncharacterized. Achieved level 2 against required level 5."
    },
